                            <comment id="13641102" author="alangates" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2013 22:44:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch that puts the tests in a parallel structure so that each one is run.  Tests are still run serially by setting parallelism to 1, but a side effect of parallel is that each of its components is run even if one of them fails.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13643275" author="sushanth" created="Fri, 26 Apr 2013 21:50:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good to me, I&apos;ve faked a test failure and am running tests. If tests continue to run, I will go ahead and commit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One important note to people visiting this bug later - the patch provided is for hcatalog/build.xml, not the root build.xml.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13643314" author="sushanth" created="Fri, 26 Apr 2013 22:24:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tested, works, and in fact, will also bypass and continue if there is a compile error in one group of tests. Potent! I&apos;m waiting for the test run to finish to see if the overall test task results in a &quot;BUILD SUCCESSFUL&quot;(not expected) or a &quot;BUILD FAILURE&quot;(expected).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13643343" author="sushanth" created="Fri, 26 Apr 2013 22:57:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, tests ran fully and ended with a BUILD FAILURE. Will commit to 0.11 and trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
